text.tspan: The intermission logo is comprised of one colour, a CMYK black. The logo lives with an
addition of 16 dots, aligned with the tittles of of the last two “i”s in the wordmark. The grid
system is operated on a 1/0.5 in measurement.
The grid system must operate on a whole or 0.5 inch measurement. The only time a 0.25 inch
measure may be applied is when the grid is less than 1x1 inch. The grid may never exist at any
other measurement than
or
The logo also exists without the dots, as just the wordmark in the example on the left. This logo
must always be paired with the grid system. The grid system, as specified with the original
logo, must operate on either a whole or .5 number of inches. No other division is possible.
The logo, when placed inside the grid, must have a boundry box determined by the measure
of the grid. The box must take up 7x4 grid squares, regardless of the size of the grid. The logo
must be adjusted and sized accordingly. The grid must line up with the tittles of the “i”s.
Do not allow the grid to bleed into the logo. Do not alter the positioning of the logo within the
grid, and do not resize the logo larger than as specified.
Do not add colour to the logo. Do not add a gradient of any kind to the logo. Do not intrude
upon the logo’s safe zone.
When placed on a black background, the logo may be knocked-out in white only. All rules still
apply to the logo within the grid.
There is a system of 5 shapes used for the visuals surrounding the logo of The Intermission.
These five shapes may be used in conjunction with the grid, but may never exist on the
stand-alone logomark.
In addition to the shapes there is a set of 6 colours that may be used. Do not alter these
colours, or add any new colours to the set.
Of the colours, the first five are used for illustration purposes, the final colour is used as a text
accent, and shall
never
be applied to any of the shapes.

svg.text: To generate more colours, this set may be overlayed with one another to produce mixes.

With Shapes
The shapes can be scaled freely within the space, but there must
be one dominant shape. No shapes may directly interact with The
Intermission logo mark when placed inside the grid. The shapes
must align to the grid squares.
